&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You will be responsible for assisting with securing competitive initial pricing, tracking early-stage sample development, and building the financial and operational frameworks (assisting with P&amp;amp;Ls and Time &amp;amp; Action calendars) needed to successfully launch new projects. The ideal candidate has strong financial acumen, excellent project management skills, and experience communicating with factories across Asia and Central America.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Costing &amp;amp; Financial Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;

&lt;h1 data-start=&quot;163&quot; data-end=&quot;240&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;165&quot; data-end=&quot;240&quot;&gt;Build Your Sales Career at One of America’s Fastest-Growing Startups&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hey! I am &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/mahak-sethi-a76751b7/&quot;&gt;Mahak&lt;/a&gt;. In 2022, I was an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant Professor&lt;/strong&gt; pursuing a &lt;strong&gt;PhD in Finance&lt;/strong&gt;. That was the &quot;big career.&quot; If you told me then I’d end up in Sales, I would’ve lectured you for an hour on why I was meant for a classroom, not a CRM. I was playing it safe in academia, convinced I’d reached the pinnacle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then I joined Fresh Prints in December 2022. It was a total U-turn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I went from &quot;Professor Mahak&quot; to a &lt;strong&gt;Junior ISA&lt;/strong&gt;. On paper, it looked like a massive step backward. A total entry-level grind after years of academic prestige. My ego took a hit. I was starting from scratch in a field that used to terrify me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;But Day 1 was a reality check.&lt;/strong&gt; I saw 21-year-olds demolishing their goals with a level of fire I’d never seen in a lecture hall. I realized my degrees didn&#39;t matter as much as my drive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Memory: The Sunday Morning Email: &lt;/strong&gt;A few weeks in, I got a team-wide email from &lt;strong&gt;Jacob (our Co-Founder)&lt;/strong&gt; titled &lt;em&gt;“How to establish a great first connection.”&lt;/em&gt; I opened it and froze. He used an email I had sent to a client as the perfect example of what &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; to do. :’)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It was a tough pill to swallow. I was devastated, but also shocked. I had no idea the leadership was watching so closely or cared that much about an entry-level associate&#39;s growth. I didn&#39;t quit; I reflected. Jacob kept working with me because he saw me actually listening. Exactly one month later, Jacob shared a new example of perfect client communication with the team. &lt;strong&gt;This time, it was me.&lt;/strong&gt; I traded the lecture notes for a headset and stepped into the limelight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seven months in? Promoted to Level I. A year later, my boss, Dylan, asked the ultimate question: &lt;em&gt;“Do you want to grow as a solo contributor, or do you want to lead?”&lt;/em&gt; Most people would’ve asked for a manual or a training week. I just felt electric. I’d led clubs in college and always had that &quot;Commander&quot; energy; I just never knew a corporate job would actually let me unleash it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I didn’t just swim; I built a fleet. Within 10 months, I was promoted to &lt;strong&gt;Inside Sales Manager&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, my &quot;PhD&quot; stands for &lt;strong&gt;Powerhouse Development&lt;/strong&gt; (haha, jk!). My day-to-day isn&#39;t just management; it’s about architecting the success of my team. I work directly with my ISAs to dismantle their targets, build closing strategies, and turn Junior ISAs into Key Account Managers who scale business through high-value referrals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fresh Prints is a high-speed experiment in autonomy. I went from teaching theory to driving real-world impact, and I haven&#39;t looked back since.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you have the energy to build, experiment, and own outcomes, I’d love to hear from you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
