&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the IT backbone for a 75-person fully remote company, growing conservatively over the next 12 months. You will own end-to-end IT operations — from the laptop that shows up at a new hire&#39;s door, to the automations that provision their accounts, to the LLM-powered internal tools that make the whole function scale. You will also own day-to-day IT compliance and governance execution in partnership with the Director of InfoSec. This is a builder&#39;s role wearing a support hat, not the other way around.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run day-to-day IT help desk for ~75 employees (and growing), resolving 75+ tickets per week across software access, account provisioning, laptop issues, and general IT support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full laptop lifecycle — vendor pricing, procurement, Kandji-managed deployment, refreshes, and retrieval from voluntary and involuntary terminations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain automations across Zapier, Okta, Google Workspace, Jira, and Slack to eliminate repetitive IT work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop internal tools and scripts that call LLM APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini) to automate ticket triage, documentation, onboarding checklists, and other IT workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute IT compliance and governance work in partnership with the Director of InfoSec — access reviews, evidence collection for SOC 2 and similar audits, policy enforcement in Okta and Kandji, and offboarding ve

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Frontier&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frontier&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a subsidiary of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Fresh Prints&lt;/strong&gt;. Fresh Prints is a New York-based, fast-growing, fully remote, 150-person company with most of our team based in India and the Philippines. A few years ago, Fresh Prints began helping other fast-growing companies build their teams. We got so good at it that we spun out a new company to focus exclusively on that — and called it&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Frontier&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
